# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Household FIRE Planner — environment variables
#
# Copy this file to `.env.local` for local development and fill in real values.
# `.env.local` is gitignored and must NEVER be committed.
#
# In production (Vercel), set these under: Project → Settings → Environment Variables.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_* vars are baked in at BUILD time — changing one requires a redeploy.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# --- Supabase (auth + cloud sync) -------------------------------------------
# From Supabase dashboard → Project Settings → API.
# Both are exposed to the browser. The anon key is public-safe (Row Level
# Security enforces access); the service-role key is NOT used by this app and
# must never be added here.
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project-ref.supabase.co
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-supabase-anon-public-key

# --- Site URL (SEO) ----------------------------------------------------------
# Production origin, NO trailing slash. Drives metadataBase, canonical/OpenGraph
# URLs (src/app/layout.tsx), sitemap.xml (src/app/sitemap.ts) and robots.txt
# (src/app/robots.ts). If unset, the code falls back to http://localhost:3000,
# so this MUST be set in production or the sitemap will point at localhost.
NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL=https://www.yourdomain.com

# --- Market data (server-side price/symbol API) ------------------------------
# Used by src/app/api/prices and src/app/api/symbols. Server-only secrets —
# NOT prefixed with NEXT_PUBLIC, so they never reach the browser.
EODHD_API_KEY=your-eodhd-api-key
MARKET_DATA_PROVIDER=eodhd

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Supabase Edge Function secrets (NOT Vercel / Next.js env vars)
#
# These belong to the `notify-feedback` edge function and are set with
# `supabase secrets set NAME=value`, NOT in `.env.local` or Vercel. Listed here
# for completeness — see DEPLOYMENT.md "Email notifications for feedback".
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# RESEND_API_KEY=re_xxxxxxxxxxxx          # Resend API key (sending access)
# FEEDBACK_WEBHOOK_SECRET=                # shared secret guarding the webhook
# FEEDBACK_TO_EMAIL=zhchong0623@gmail.com # where feedback is delivered
# FEEDBACK_FROM_EMAIL=noreply@yourdomain.com  # sender once your domain is verified in Resend
